abstract: Supreme Court declines to hear challenge to Wisconsin law requiring voters to provide photo identification before casting their ballots; state officials say they will not enforce law in April 7 election, but will require compliance in later ones.
lead_paragraph: After the Supreme Court rejected a challenge to the law, one of the strictest in the nation, Wisconsin officials said they would wait until the next election to enforce it.

headline.main: Wisconsin Decides Not to Enforce Voter ID Law
headline.print_headline: Justices Decline to Hear Challenge to Wisconsin’s Voter ID Law
